'''Moon Studios GmbH''' is an Austrian [[video game developer]] founded in 2010 and based in [[Vienna]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/242530/Postmortem_Moon_Studios_heartfelt_Ori_and_the_Blind_Forest.php | title = Postmortem: Moon Studios' heartfelt ''Ori and the Blind Forest'' | last = Mahler | first = Thomas | date = 5 May 2015 | website = [[Gamasutra]] | publisher = [[UBM TechWeb]] | accessdate = 27 April 2016}}</ref> They are best known for their 2015 title ''[[Ori and the Blind Forest]]'', for which the studio was awarded the Best Debut award at the 2016 [[Game Developers Choice Awards]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gdconf.com/news/witcher_3_wins_game_of_the_yea.html |title=''Witcher 3'' wins Game of the Year at 16th annual Game Developers Choice Awards |author=Staff |date=16 March 2016 |website=[[Game Developers Conference]] |publisher=[[UBM TechWeb]] |accessdate=27 April 2016}}</ref>

In 2011, Moon Studios signed a development and distribution deal with [[Microsoft Game Studios]] for ''[[Ori and the Blind Forest]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://refinedgeekery.com/2015/03/16/getting-to-know-moon-studios/ |title=Getting to know Moon Studios |author=Tom |date=16 March 2015 |website=[[Refined Geekery]] |accessdate=22 October 2016}}</ref> At [[E3 2017]] they announced a  sequel, ''[[Ori and the Will of the Wisps]]'', coming to Xbox One and Windows 10.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.ign.com/articles/2017/06/11/ori-and-the-will-of-the-wisps-revealed |title=ORI AND THE WILL OF THE WISPS REVEALED |author=Joe Skrebels |date=11 June 2017 |website=[[IGN]] |accessdate=15 June 2017}}</ref>

