'''Movie Furnace''' (Tanuulu) is a [[Uganda]]-based non-profit short film competition, for Mariam Ndagire Film and Performing Arts Centre alumni ([[MNFPAC]]), founded by [[Mariam Ndagire]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.monitor.co.ug/artsculture/Reviews/Nurturing-local-film-talent/-/691232/1453272/-/103tl7f/-/index.html |title=Nurturing local film talent - Reviews & Profiles |publisher=monitor.co.ug |date= |accessdate=2013-10-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.observer.ug/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=20030&catid=42&Itemid=74 |title=The Observer - Ndagire opens Tanuulu |publisher=Observer.ug |date=2012-07-26 |accessdate=2013-10-29}}</ref> The program involves film production, screenwriting, directing, cinematography, editing, sound recording and acting, The winning team headed by the director wins 1000 USD.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.monitor.co.ug/artsculture/Entertainment/-/812796/811978/-/bso3gk/-/index.html |title=Our very own screenwriter - Entertainment |publisher=monitor.co.ug |date=2009-01-20 |accessdate=2013-10-29}}</ref>
==History== [[File:Movie Furnace.JPG|thumb|left|Usama receiving his winning price]] Movie Furnace was established in 2012. The first winner was Bigaruka Hakim with his movie ''Bloody Sunset''.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.observer.ug/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=20472&catid=42&Itemid=74 |title=The Observer - Bigaruka’s Bloody Sunset wins him big |publisher=Observer.ug |date=2012-08-21 |accessdate=2013-10-29}}</ref> The second round was won by [[Usama Mukwaya]] with his film [[In Just Hours]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.observer.ug/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=26544&catid=42&Itemid=74 |title=The Observer - Mukwaya wins film contest |publisher=Observer.ug |date=2013-07-23 |accessdate=2013-10-29}}</ref> The 3rd Season was won by Sewava Ivan with his movie LIFT FROM HELL
